-- Capital Research and Management Company cuts stake in UniCredit
-- 
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 09:30AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Capital Research and Management Company, a wholly-owned subsidiary of investment manager The Capital Group, has cuts its stake in Italy's UniCredit <CRDI.MI> to 1.9 percent from 2.7 percent, according to a regulatory filing published on Thursday.

The investor has informed Italy's market watchdog Consob about the change in its stake in the Italian bank on Dec. 15.